{"title_page": "Tamara Kotevska", "text_new": "{{short description|about the Macedonian filmmaker}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Tamara Kotevska\n| image              = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u0422\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1993|8|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Prilep]], [[Republic of Macedonia]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]n\n| alma_mater         = [[Ss. Cyril and Methodius University of Skopje]]\n| occupation         = Filmmaker\n| years_active       = \n| known_for          = ''[[Honeyland (2019 film)|Honeyland]]'' (2019)\n| notable_works      = \n}}\n'''Tamara Kotevska''' ({{lang-mk|\u0422\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430}}; born 9 August 1993) is a [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]n filmmaker best known for her 2019 documentary ''[[Honeyland (2019 film)|Honeyland]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nKotevska was born in [[Prilep]], [[Republic of Macedonia]] (now [[North Macedonia]]). She earned a scholarship to study abroad in [[Tennessee]] for her junior year in high school.<ref name=\"midpoint\">{{cite web |last1= |first1= |title=Tamara Kotevska {{!}} MIDPOINT - A Training and Networking Platform for Film and TV Development |url=https://www.midpoint-center.eu/network/people/5778-tamara-kotevska |publisher=Midpoint-center.eu |accessdate=13 January 2020}}</ref> She graduated from the Faculty of Dramatic Arts at the [[Ss. Cyril and Methodius University of Skopje|Sts. Cyril and Methodius University]] in [[Skopje]],<ref name=\"povmagazine\"/> with an emphasis in documentary film.<ref>{{cite news |title=Interview: Tamara Kotevska and Ljubomir Stefanov on Making the Most Out of an Environmentally Sticky Situation in \u201cHoneyland\u201d |url=http://moveablefest.com/tamara-kotevska-ljubomir-stefanov-honeyland/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=The Moveable Fest |date=26 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nTogether with [[Ljubomir Stefanov]], Kotevska spent three years in Bekirlija, North Macedonia filming the documentary about a female wild beekeeper, Hatidze.<ref name=\"filmmaker\">{{cite news |last1= |first1= |title='Living and Working with Each Other for Those Three Years in Almost Unbearable Life Conditions': Directors Ljubo Stefanov and Tamara Kotevska {{!}} Honeyland |url=https://filmmakermagazine.com/106712-living-and-working-with-each-other-for-those-three-years-in-almost-unbearable-life-conditions-directors-ljubo-stefanov-and-tamara-kotevska-honeyland/#.XhyPx1NKgWo |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=Filmmaker Magazine |date=28 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"povmagazine\">{{cite news |title=Buzz-Worthy: Tamara Kotevska and Ljubomir Stefanov Talk \u2018Honeyland\u2019 \u2013 Point of View Magazine |last=Mullen |first=Pat |url=http://povmagazine.com/articles/view/buzz-worthy-tamara-kotevska-and-ljubomir-stefanov-talk-honeyland |accessdate=13 January 2020|date=1 August 2019 |work=Point of View Magazine  |language=en}}</ref> The film was originally going to be a documentary short about the [[Bregalnica]] river region when they came across the beekeeper.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Drury |first1=Sharareh |last2=Coates |first2=Tyler |title=Oscars: How 'Honeyland' and 'For Sama' Portray Battles on Different Fronts |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-how-honeyland-sama-portray-battles-fronts-1263514 |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=27 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Scarpa |first1=Vittoria |title=Ljubomir Stefanov, Tamara Kotevska \u2022 Directors of Honeyland |url=https://cineuropa.org/en/interview/372054/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=Cineuropa |date=10 May 2019 |language=en}}</ref> Kotevska and Stefanov previously worked together on another documentary, ''Lake of Apples'' (2017).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Eagan |first1=Daniel |title='It's a Choice: To Be a Filmmaker or a Human': Ljubomir Stefanov and Tamara Kotevska on Honeyland |url=https://filmmakermagazine.com/107983-its-a-choice-to-be-a-filmmaker-or-a-human-ljubomir-stefanov-and-tamara-kotevska-on-honeyland/#.XhyTzFNKgWo |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=Filmmaker Magazine |date=22 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n''Honeyland'' won three awards at the [[2019 Sundance Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite news |title=2019 Sundance Film Festival Awards Announced |url=https://www.sundance.org/blogs/news/2019-sundance-film-festival-awards-announced |accessdate=13 January 2020 |publisher=Sundance Institute|date=3 February 2019 |language=English}}</ref> and received two nominations at the [[92nd Academy Awards]]: [[Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature|Best Documentary Feature]] and [[Academy Award for Best International Feature Film|Best International Feature Film]]. It is the second Macedonian film to earn an Oscar nomination after ''[[Before the Rain (1994 film)|Before the Rain]]'' (1994).<ref name=\"oscarnom\">{{cite news |title=Oscar nominations 2020: \u2018Joker\u2019 leads with 11; Greta Gerwig snubbed for best director; complete list of nominees |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/arts-entertainment/2020/01/13/oscar-nominations-2020/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=The Washington Post |date=13 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u201e\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u201c \u0441\u043e \u0434\u0432\u0435 \u043d\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u201e\u041e\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0440\u201c |url=https://republika.mk/vesti/kultura/medena-zemja-so-dve-nominacii-za-oskar-2/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=\u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 |date=13 January 2020 |language=mk-MK}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb name|nm9393813}}\n\n{{Authority control|VIAF=2157769907748660150}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kotevska, Tamara}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Prilep]]\n[[Category:Macedonian documentary filmmakers]]\n[[Category:Macedonian film directors]]\n[[Category:Women documentary filmmakers]]\n[[Category:Ss. Cyril and Methodius University of Skopje alumni]]\n{{NorthMacedonia-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|about the North Macedonian filmmaker}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Tamara Kotevska\n| image              = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u0422\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1993|8|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Prilep]], [[Republic of Macedonia]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]n\n| alma_mater         = [[Ss. Cyril and Methodius University of Skopje]]\n| occupation         = Filmmaker\n| years_active       = \n| known_for          = ''[[Honeyland (2019 film)|Honeyland]]'' (2019)\n| notable_works      = \n}}\n'''Tamara Kotevska''' ({{lang-mk|\u0422\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430}}; born 9 August 1993) is a [[North Macedonia|Macedonia]]n filmmaker best known for her 2019 documentary ''[[Honeyland (2019 film)|Honeyland]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nKotevska was born in [[Prilep]], [[Republic of Macedonia]] (now [[North Macedonia]]). She earned a scholarship to study abroad in [[Tennessee]] for her junior year in high school.<ref name=\"midpoint\">{{cite web |last1= |first1= |title=Tamara Kotevska {{!}} MIDPOINT - A Training and Networking Platform for Film and TV Development |url=https://www.midpoint-center.eu/network/people/5778-tamara-kotevska |publisher=Midpoint-center.eu |accessdate=13 January 2020}}</ref> She graduated from the Faculty of Dramatic Arts at the [[Ss. Cyril and Methodius University of Skopje|Sts. Cyril and Methodius University]] in [[Skopje]],<ref name=\"povmagazine\"/> with an emphasis in documentary film.<ref>{{cite news |title=Interview: Tamara Kotevska and Ljubomir Stefanov on Making the Most Out of an Environmentally Sticky Situation in \u201cHoneyland\u201d |url=http://moveablefest.com/tamara-kotevska-ljubomir-stefanov-honeyland/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=The Moveable Fest |date=26 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nTogether with [[Ljubomir Stefanov]], Kotevska spent three years in Bekirlija, North Macedonia filming the documentary about a female wild beekeeper, Hatidze.<ref name=\"filmmaker\">{{cite news |last1= |first1= |title='Living and Working with Each Other for Those Three Years in Almost Unbearable Life Conditions': Directors Ljubo Stefanov and Tamara Kotevska {{!}} Honeyland |url=https://filmmakermagazine.com/106712-living-and-working-with-each-other-for-those-three-years-in-almost-unbearable-life-conditions-directors-ljubo-stefanov-and-tamara-kotevska-honeyland/#.XhyPx1NKgWo |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=Filmmaker Magazine |date=28 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"povmagazine\">{{cite news |title=Buzz-Worthy: Tamara Kotevska and Ljubomir Stefanov Talk \u2018Honeyland\u2019 \u2013 Point of View Magazine |last=Mullen |first=Pat |url=http://povmagazine.com/articles/view/buzz-worthy-tamara-kotevska-and-ljubomir-stefanov-talk-honeyland |accessdate=13 January 2020|date=1 August 2019 |work=Point of View Magazine  |language=en}}</ref> The film was originally going to be a documentary short about the [[Bregalnica]] river region when they came across the beekeeper.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Drury |first1=Sharareh |last2=Coates |first2=Tyler |title=Oscars: How 'Honeyland' and 'For Sama' Portray Battles on Different Fronts |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-how-honeyland-sama-portray-battles-fronts-1263514 |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=27 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Scarpa |first1=Vittoria |title=Ljubomir Stefanov, Tamara Kotevska \u2022 Directors of Honeyland |url=https://cineuropa.org/en/interview/372054/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=Cineuropa |date=10 May 2019 |language=en}}</ref> Kotevska and Stefanov previously worked together on another documentary, ''Lake of Apples'' (2017).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Eagan |first1=Daniel |title='It's a Choice: To Be a Filmmaker or a Human': Ljubomir Stefanov and Tamara Kotevska on Honeyland |url=https://filmmakermagazine.com/107983-its-a-choice-to-be-a-filmmaker-or-a-human-ljubomir-stefanov-and-tamara-kotevska-on-honeyland/#.XhyTzFNKgWo |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=Filmmaker Magazine |date=22 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n''Honeyland'' won three awards at the [[2019 Sundance Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite news |title=2019 Sundance Film Festival Awards Announced |url=https://www.sundance.org/blogs/news/2019-sundance-film-festival-awards-announced |accessdate=13 January 2020 |publisher=Sundance Institute|date=3 February 2019 |language=English}}</ref> and received two nominations at the [[92nd Academy Awards]]: [[Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature|Best Documentary Feature]] and [[Academy Award for Best International Feature Film|Best International Feature Film]]. It is the second Macedonian film to earn an Oscar nomination after ''[[Before the Rain (1994 film)|Before the Rain]]'' (1994).<ref name=\"oscarnom\">{{cite news |title=Oscar nominations 2020: \u2018Joker\u2019 leads with 11; Greta Gerwig snubbed for best director; complete list of nominees |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/arts-entertainment/2020/01/13/oscar-nominations-2020/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=The Washington Post |date=13 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u201e\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u201c \u0441\u043e \u0434\u0432\u0435 \u043d\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d\